===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small [[mammal]], of the family [[Erinaceidae]] or subfamily [[Erinaceinae]] ({{vern|spiny hedgehog|pl=s}}, the latter characterized by their [[spiny]] back and often by the habit of rolling up into a ball when attacked.)
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Tempest|act=II|scene=ii|page=9|column=1|passage=[L]ike '''Hedg-hogs''' vvhich / Lye tumbling in my bare-foote vvay, and mount / Their pricks at my foot-fall: ſometime am I / All vvound vvith Adders, vvho vvith clouen tongues / Doe hiſſe me into madneſſe: {{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|US}} Any of several spiny mammals, such as the porcupine, that are similar to the hedgehog.
# {{lb|en|military}} {{ellipsis of|en|Czech hedgehog}}: a type of moveable military [[barricade]] made.
#* {{quote-web|en|url=https://www.npr.org/2022/03/21/1086709135/russia-ukraine-war-military-terms-lingo-phrases|text=Ukrainian civilians have been DIY-ing '''hedgehogs''', welding two bars or beams at an angle to make a cross and then adding a third to ensure it holds its shape even if it's knocked over.|date=2022-03-21|accessdate=2022-03-21|author=Bill Chappell|publisher={{w|NPR}}|work=SPECIAL SERIES: Ukraine invasion&nbsp;— explained|title=SWIFT, hedgehog, MiG: Here's a guide to the terms of war in Ukraine}}
# {{lb|en|informal|military|historical}} A [[spigot]] [[mortar]]-type of [[depth charge]] weapon from [[World War II]] that simultaneously fires a number of explosives into the water to create a pattern of underwater [[explosion]]s intended to attack submerged [[submarine]]s. [[Category:en:World War II]]
# {{lb|en|Australia}} A type of chocolate cake (or [[slice]]), somewhat similar to an American [[brownie]].
#* '''2005''', Paul Mitchell, ''The Favourite'', Frank Moorhouse, ''The Best Australian Stories 2005'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=OBRMpu_VrysC&pg=PA145 page 145],
#*: There are '''hedgehogs''' with sultanas as well as breadcrumbs, carrot cakes and fruitcakes and banana walnut loaves.
#* '''2008''', Lili Wilkinson, ''The Not Quite Perfect Boyfriend'', [https://books.google.com/books?id=yX8LNt4ErAsC&pg=PT13 unnumbered page],
#*: I am so flustered that I order a vanilla slice instead of '''hedgehog'''.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=2009|author=[[w:Adam Shand (journalist)|Adam Shand]]|title=The Skull: Informers, Hit Men and Australia's Toughest Cop|page=199|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=fLBaR8rAJEoC&pg=PA199|passage=His wife had made a '''hedgehog''' cake and he offered some but Murphy refused – his mouth was so dry with terror he couldn′t swallow.}}
# A form of dredging machine.
#* '''1868''', "Dredging," article in Charles Tomlinson (editor), ''Cyclopædia of Useful Arts, Mechanical and Chemical, Manufactures, Mining, and Engineering'', Volume 1, [https://books.google.com/books?id=KDJRAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA520 page 520],
#*: The first machines merely loosened, but did not raise the stuff, a scouring being afterwards effected by means of sluices. These machines consisted of large bars or prongs placed vertically in a frame, and being fastened to a barge placed in the line of the sluices, the whole was inpelled forward by the current, thereby scouring the bed. Such a machine, called a '''''hedgehog''''', is still used in Lincolnshire.
# Certain [[flowering plant]]s with parts resembling a member of family [[Erinaceidae]]
## {{taxlink|Medicago intertexta|species|ver=161014}}, the pods of which are armed with short spines.
## {{taxlink|Retzia capensis|species|ver=171228}} of South Africa.
# The [[edible]] [[fungus]] ''[[Hydnum repandum]]''.
#: {{synonyms|en|sweet tooth|wood hedgehog}}
#* '''1998''', Randy Molina, David Pilz, ''Managing Forest Ecosystems to Conserve Fungus Diversity and Sustain Wild Mushroom Harvests''
#*: '''Hedgehogs''' fruit from autumn until late spring. Many consumers are still unfamiliar with '''hedgehogs''', and they have a relatively small commercial trade.
# A kind of [[electrical]] [[transformer]] with open magnetic circuit, the ends of the iron wire core being turned outward and presenting a bristling appearance.
# A way of serving [[food]] at a [[party]], consisting of a half [[melon]] or [[potato]] etc. with individual [[cocktail stick]]s of [[cheese]] and [[pineapple]] stuck into it.
# {{lb|en|differential geometry}} A type of [[plane curve]]; see {{w|Hedgehog (geometry)}}. [[Category:en:Curves]]

